BULLETIN - EAS ACTIVATION REQUESTED
CHILD ABDUCTION EMERGENCY
TEXAS DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC SAFETY
RELAYED BY NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE FORT WORTH TX
944 PM CDT FRI SEP 17 2021

THE FOLLOWING MESSAGE IS TRANSMITTED AT THE REQUEST OF THE TEXAS
DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC SAFETY.

THIS IS A CHILD ABDUCTION ALERT ISSUED BY THE TEXAS AMBER ALERT
NETWORK. 

THE JUDSON I S D POLICE DEPARTMENT IS SEARCHING FOR ALHEIRIE
RODRIGUEZ POMALES, HISPANIC, FEMALE, 12 YEARS OLD, 5 FOOT ZERO
INCHES, 100 POUNDS, BROWN HAIR, BROWN EYES, AND WEARING A BLACK
PULLOVER SHIRT, BLACK PANTS, CARRYING A PINK AND GRAY BACKPACK.

POLICE ARE LOOKING FOR MARIE RODRIGUEZ POMALES, HISPANIC, FEMALE,
28 YEARS OLD, 5 FOOT ZERO INCHES, 120 POUNDS, BROWN HAIR, BROWN 
EYES IN CONNECTION WITH HER ABDUCTION.

THE SUSPECT WAS LAST HEARD FROM IN CONVERSE, TX.

LAW ENFORCEMENT OFFICIALS BELIEVE THIS CHILD TO BE IN GRAVE OR
IMMEDIATE DANGER.

IF YOU HAVE ANY INFORMATION REGARDING THIS ABDUCTION, CALL THE
JUDSON ISD POLICE DEPARTMENT AT 2 1 0 6 5 9 9 7 8 9. 

THE NEWS MEDIA POINT OF CONTACT IS JUDSON ISD POLICE DEPARTMENT
AT 2 1 0 6 5 9 9 7 8 9.

 

$
